other_tests.findings: Mixed axonal and demyelinating sensory motor polyneuropathy with reduced compound muscle action potentials and reduced or absent sensory nerve action potential, prolonged F-wave latencies, and reduced motor nerve conduction velocity.
Increased echogenicity of median and ulnar nerves at the right arm, and peroneal and tibial nerves at the left, with loss of typical honeycomb-like pattern, indicating minifascicles.
Patient 1: Invasive seminoma with loss of seminiferous tubules and Leydig cells. Patient 2: Atypical proliferating cells indicative of seminoma in situ with beginning invasion.
